menu "PMW3360 runtime behaviors"

config ZMK_BEHAVIOR_PMW3360_RUNTIME_HOOKS
    bool
    default y
    help
      Build the weak runtime hook implementation used by the PMW3360 runtime
      tuning behaviors.

      Boards may override the hook with a strong symbol to trigger custom
      status updates or visual feedback whenever CPI or burst accumulation is
      changed at runtime.

config ZMK_BEHAVIOR_PMW3360_RUNTIME_PERSISTENCE
    bool
    default y
    depends on INPUT_PIXART_PMW3360 && SETTINGS
    help
      Enable PMW3360 runtime tuning persistence through Zephyr settings.

      This stores and restores the currently selected CPI and burst
      accumulation values for the convenience behaviors shipped by this
      module. Persisted values are restored after boot and after firmware
      reflash as long as the keyboard settings storage is preserved.

config ZMK_BEHAVIOR_PMW3360_CPI_CYCLE
    bool "PMW3360 CPI cycle behavior"
    default y
    depends on INPUT_PIXART_PMW3360
    help
      Expose a directly usable ZMK behavior that cycles PMW3360 CPI values at
      runtime.

      This behavior assumes a single enabled PMW3360 device in the build and
      is intended for keymap-level runtime tuning such as CPI up/down buttons.

config ZMK_BEHAVIOR_PMW3360_BURST_ACCUMULATION_CYCLE
    bool "PMW3360 burst accumulation cycle behavior"
    default y
    depends on INPUT_PIXART_PMW3360
    help
      Expose a directly usable ZMK behavior that cycles the PMW3360 burst
      accumulation limit at runtime.

      This is primarily useful on BLE pointing builds where one-burst-per-HID-
      report can create visible report backlog under fast motion.

config ZMK_BEHAVIOR_PMW3360_SAVE_SETTINGS
    bool "PMW3360 save runtime settings behavior"
    default y
    depends on INPUT_PIXART_PMW3360 && SETTINGS
    select ZMK_BEHAVIOR_PMW3360_RUNTIME_PERSISTENCE
    help
      Expose a directly usable ZMK behavior that saves the current PMW3360
      runtime CPI and burst accumulation values to persistent settings.

      This is intended for keymaps that want an explicit "commit current PMW
      tuning" action instead of writing to flash on every CPI or burst
      accumulation change.

endmenu
